# .envrc.example
#
# Example environment configuration for Artifact Review project.
# Copy this to `.envrc` and configure with your actual values.
#
# This file uses direnv (https://direnv.net) for automatic environment management.
# Install direnv and run `direnv allow .` to enable.

# Inherit from parent directory (if you have organization-wide env vars)
source_up

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local Development Environment Variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are typically auto-generated by `npx convex dev` into `.env.local`
# You don't need to set them manually unless troubleshooting.

# Convex Development Deployment
# Auto-generated by: npx convex dev
# export CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:your-deployment-name
# export NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-dev-deployment.convex.cloud

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: Development Tools
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# GitHub CLI (optional - uses separate `gh auth login`)
# export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...

# Vercel CLI (optional - uses separate `vercel login`)
# export VERCEL_TOKEN=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Local Development:
# - Run `npx convex dev` to auto-generate .env.local with Convex credentials
# - Mailpit runs via Docker (no env vars needed)
# - OAuth apps use localhost redirect URLs
#
# Environment Variables NOT stored here:
# - Resend API keys → Set in Convex via `npx convex env set`
# - OAuth secrets → Set in Convex via `npx convex env set`
# - Vercel deploy keys → Set in Vercel dashboard
# - Production credentials → Never in local environment
#
# Security:
# - Never commit actual secrets to git
# - .envrc and .env.local are gitignored
# - Use `npx convex env set` for backend secrets
# - Use Vercel dashboard for frontend env vars
#
# See docs/setup/account-checklist.md for complete setup guide.
